				<td colspan="2"><span>The charm/kill works, I've done that. 
<br />

<br />
You can also gather up a pack of critters, face away from them (so you don't riposte accidentally), and cycle the AE slow/snare (assonance), and a couple of damage shields, and have the lowbie cast an ae or 2 (only works with those that can AE) and let the critters kill themselves on the DS.  I tried it and it kinda worked.  :p
<br />

<br />
In order to group with the bard, the toon needs to be 2/3 the level of the bard.  So, at 65, you can group with a 43 and they get exp.  I've also got a 52 monk on the same account as my bard, so I group with the monk when they get to be 34, and go smush things in OT to level 43, then swap to the bard.  i'm kinda working on a shammie atm, in between other stuff. 8)
<br />

<br />
Probably the easiest thing to do though, is twink the heck out of a toon, then when they get 20, start doing LDoN.  Doing a LDoN hard at that level is easy with twinks, and it's almost like PL. ;)</span></td>
