				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Can bards powerlevel?<a name="18762"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 3 04 12:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />
This is what you do..
<br />

<br />
Go to Unrest..
<br />

<br />
Load AE snare and run around collecting every mob you can find.
<br />
Now have your newbie hit each mob 1x via melee or spell.
<br />
Then sing veeshan/warsong and sit down over and over.
<br />
There you go... you just got some massive exp.
<br />

<br />
At higher levels it works like this...
<br />
Pull a ton of mobs AE kite them down to about 10% health (runners are the best). 
<br />
AE snare them
<br />
Hit Fading Memories
<br />
Finish them with your newbie.
<br />

<br />
The problem with this is your skills will suck when you get done.  Though it most definitly works... very well I might add.</span></td>
